I think through the years I written reviews for Yelp I've given a handful of 2 star reviews. We stopped here, very briefly, after visiting the Museum of Broadcast Industry for a coffee to take on the road. I've never been a fan of Dunkin' Donuts coffee so I ordered a hot tea.  First of all, this location is not particularly clean. But, put that aside. The others with me said their coffee was okay.  I didn't try it until we got back into our car. In my case the tea was not exactly what I expected. One would think they would take hot water and put a tea bag in it. But, noooo. Here, they brew the tea and leave it sitting all day long. From what I can tell, I guess not too many people order tea.Yes, it tasted like it sat on a heat source all day long. It was completely undrinkable.  If the others with me had a similar experience, this probably would have been one star only. But, since the coffee was drinkable, two stars. This was really disappointing.
